
                                            Twelve children and the driver of the scholar transport have been hospitalised.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - Two children have been killed in a crash in Benoni on the East Rand on Wednesday morning.  It is understood that the driver of the vehicle, carrying 14 pupils, lost control and collided with a car before rolling several times.  Twelve children and the driver of the scholar transport have been hospitalised. Ekurhuleni emergency service's William Ntladi: "The driver of the scholar transport lost control, hit a lamp post and the vehicle rolled several times. Two children were killed instantly."